Text: Aam Aadmi Party's rebel leader, Shanti Bhushan, has criticized Kejriwal for betraying Anna Hazare's betrayal by Kejriwal by taking a false step in the fodder scam of Kejriwal-Lalu. Anna Hazare had formed the foundation for the establishment of Kejriwal's Aam Aadmi Party by anti-corruption movement. Arvind Kejriwal was stuck in politics and he became the Delhi Chief Minister. However, Shanti Bhushan criticized Kejriwal for being forgetful about the dream that Kejriwal has forgotten his dream, and said that Kejriwal is a dictator. Shanti Bhushan alleged that Kejriwal had shown the same to Laloo Prasad Yadav, the accused in the fodder scam during Nitish Kumar's swearing-in ceremony. Bhushan, one of the founding members of the country's former law minister and its founder, has alleged that Kejriwal is acting as a Khap Panchayat. However, Lalu Yadav, former Bihar chief minister, took Kejriwal's coercion and forced Kejriwal to hug Laloo in the absence of political motivation.

Text: Pak violates ceasefire once again In Poonch district of Jammu, Pakistani troops once again violated the Armed Forces by firing on the Line of Control (LoC) Indian posts. Srinagar: Pakistani troops once again violated arms and ammunition in Poonch district of Jammu by firing at Indian positions on Line of Control (LoC). On Saturday night, they started fierce firing. Indian troops also responded to the firing by launching Pakistani troops in the Indian posts of Shahapur sector of Poonch district. The firing started from the Pakistani army till four o'clock in the morning. No Indian soldier was injured in the firing, military officials said. A search operation was launched in several areas due to the firing on Saturday.
